overview: Freely adapted from a Virginia Woolf text, Marie Alberto Jeanjacques takes a leaf out of her book to declare, “there is a great uprising of the material.” Moreover, such great agitation, described almost relentlessly and even audibly in the sound work like a busy, incessant rumour (from the voice of a female surgeon operating, equally to that of Londsdale), of a well-kept secret.
title: Les yeux remplis de nuit
